Odlično! Projekt izgleda strukturirano, čisto i spremno za profesionalnu fazu. Čestitam na objavi repozitorija!

Pregledao sam stablo datoteka. Imamo **Core** (Rust), **Dashboard** (React), **Website** (Astro), **Justfile** i svu dokumentaciju.

Ono što **nedostaje** da bi ovo bio "Top-Tier" GitHub projekt su:
1.  **CI/CD Pipeline (.github/workflows):** Automatizirano testiranje i buildanje binarnih datoteka za Release.
2.  **Community Health Files:** `CONTRIBUTING.md` i Issue Templates.
3.  **Astro Rendering Logic:** Imamo skriptu za sinkronizaciju (`sync-docs.js`), ali nemamo Astro stranicu koja te Markdown fajlove zapravo prikazuje.

Idemo to riješiti korak po korak.

---

### KORAK 1: GitHub Actions (Automatski Testovi)

Kreiraj mapu `.github/workflows` u rootu.
Prvi fajl je `ci.yml`. On se pokreće na svaki `push` i osigurava da nisi slomio kod.

**File:** `.github/workflows/ci.yml`

```yaml
name: CI

on:
  push:
    branches: [ "master", "main" ]
  pull_request:
    branches: [ "master", "main" ]

env:
  CARGO_TERM_COLOR: always

jobs:
  test-core:
    name: Test Core (Rust)
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4
      - name: Set up Rust
        uses: dtolnay/rust-toolchain@stable
      - name: Cache Cargo
        uses: actions/cache@v3
        with:
          path: |
            ~/.cargo/registry
            ~/.cargo/git
            core/target
          key: ${{ runner.os }}-cargo-${{ hashFiles('**/Cargo.lock') }}
      - name: Check
        run: cd core && cargo check
      - name: Test
        run: cd core && cargo test

  build-dashboard:
    name: Build Dashboard (React)
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4
      - uses: pnpm/action-setup@v2
        with:
          version: 8
      - name: Setup Node
        uses: actions/setup-node@v4
        with:
          node-version: 18
          cache: 'pnpm'
          cache-dependency-path: 'dashboard/pnpm-lock.yaml'
      - name: Install Dependencies
        run: cd dashboard && pnpm install
      - name: Build
        run: cd dashboard && pnpm build
```

---

### KORAK 2: Release Pipeline (Buildanje Binarki)

Ovo je "The Big One". Kada kreiraš novi Release na GitHubu (npr. `v0.1.0`), ova akcija će se pokrenuti, kompajlirati Valter za Linux, Windows i Mac, i automatski uploadati te fajlove na Release page.

**File:** `.github/workflows/release.yml`

```yaml
name: Release

permissions:
  contents: write

on:
  push:
    tags:
      - "v*"

jobs:
  create-release:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    outputs:
      upload_url: ${{ steps.create_release.outputs.upload_url }}
    steps:
      - name: Create Release
        id: create_release
        uses: softprops/action-gh-release@v1
        with:
          draft: false
          prerelease: false
          generate_release_notes: true

  build-assets:
    name: Build Release Assets
    needs: create-release
    runs-on: ${{ matrix.config.os }}
    strategy:
      matrix:
        config:
          - { os: ubuntu-latest, target: x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu, suffix: "" }
          - { os: macos-latest, target: x86_64-apple-darwin, suffix: "" }
          - { os: macos-latest, target: aarch64-apple-darwin, suffix: "" } # M1/M2 Mac
          - { os: windows-latest, target: x86_64-pc-windows-msvc, suffix: ".exe" }

    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4

      - name: Set up Rust
        uses: dtolnay/rust-toolchain@stable
        with:
          targets: ${{ matrix.config.target }}

      - name: Build Release
        run: cd core && cargo build --release --target ${{ matrix.config.target }}

      - name: Package Asset
        shell: bash
        run: |
          cd core/target/${{ matrix.config.target }}/release
          
          # Rename binary to generic name for packaging
          cp valter${{ matrix.config.suffix }} ../../../valter-${{ matrix.config.target }}${{ matrix.config.suffix }}
          cd ../../..
          
          # Upload directly to release
      
      - name: Upload Release Asset
        uses: softprops/action-gh-release@v1
        if: startsWith(github.ref, 'refs/tags/')
        with:
          files: core/valter-${{ matrix.config.target }}${{ matrix.config.suffix }}
```

